  "dataFlow": "User submits a GitHub repo URL + brief via the Next.js dashboard (or via Linear/GitHub webhook, or autonomy poller). The request hits POST /api/build on the FastAPI backend (auth via HttpOnly HMAC cookie). create_session() allocates a BuildSession in the in-memory _sessions dict and persists it to disk via os.replace(). run_build() launches as an asyncio task: it clones the repo into app/workspaces/{sid}/, runs the 5-phase pipeline (plan→generate→evaluate→test→ship) via ClaudeSDKClient with bypassPermissions, appends structured events to session.output_lines, and writes phase checkpoints atomically. The browser receives live output via WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} or SSE /api/sessions/{sid}/logs polling output_lines with a 150-300ms tick. On completion, session status transitions to 'complete'/'failed' and the final state is persisted. Observability events (gate_checks, costs) are written fire-and-forget to Supabase via supabase_log.py. Pi-SEO scanner results land in .harness/scan-results/ and are read by the monitor agent to produce .harness/monitor-digests/ JSON. The MCP server reads .harness/ files directly for Claude Desktop integration. Telegram inbound messages flow: Telegram→getUpdates polling→.harness/telegram-inbox/→watchdog drain→route classification→.harness/ideas-from-phone/ or self-heal action. Critical alerts flow: triage engine→supabase alert_escalations table→30-min watchdog escalation coroutine→Telegram sendMessage.",
